whatever you want.

35:23.304 --> 35:27.074
But I can't handle this.
Can you understand that, Denise?

35:27.141 --> 35:30.177
<i>I-I can't deal
with having this child.</i>

35:32.146 --> 35:34.048
I don't have the strength.

35:39.753 --> 35:42.389
[ Bell Dings ]

35:42.456 --> 35:44.391
Hi.
Hi, Wayne.

35:44.458 --> 35:47.161
Where are you going?
Down to pathology.

35:47.228 --> 35:49.163
This elevator's
going up, Cathy.

35:49.230 --> 35:51.966
Oh. I do that
all the time.

35:52.032 --> 35:54.134
You come here often?
[ chuckles ]

35:54.201 --> 35:57.137
I enjoyed the pistol range.
Did you really?

35:57.204 --> 36:00.774
Sure. If I'm ever attacked
by a paper target,
I'll be ready.

36:00.841 --> 36:03.911
So, uh,
you're on call tonight?
Yeah.

36:03.978 --> 36:06.380
Head-On collision.
It's got me swamped.

36:06.447 --> 36:09.216
I can come down
a little later
and give you a hand.

36:09.283 --> 36:12.253
Thanks, Wayne, but no.

36:12.319 --> 36:14.755
<i>[ motor stops ]
What happened?</i>

36:14.822 --> 36:18.626
Well, it appears that
we're stuck.

36:18.692 --> 36:21.128
This happens on an average
of about twice a week.

36:21.195 --> 36:26.066
No. No, you don't understand.
Elevators make me nervous
enough when they're moving.

36:26.133 --> 36:29.336
I feel so strange
in elevators.

36:29.403 --> 36:33.407
I never know where to look.
I know. My elevator etiquette
isn't too good either.

36:33.474 --> 36:36.443
I always think
Everyone's looking at me,

36:36.510 --> 36:38.679
staring at me,

36:38.746 --> 36:41.415
undressing me
with their eyes.

36:41.482 --> 36:46.053
I don't think, uh,
everybody does that.

36:46.120 --> 36:50.691
Now we're trapped, Wayne.
It may take them hours
to discover us,

36:50.758 --> 36:55.129
like the blackout
in manhattan, 1979.

36:55.195 --> 36:58.966
I was stuck in an elevator
at the biltmore--
Cathy--

36:59.033 --> 37:03.504
With an arab Prince
and four labradors.

37:03.571 --> 37:05.506
No.
Take it easy.

37:05.573 --> 37:07.608
Hold me, Wayne!
Please hold me.

37:07.675 --> 37:10.277
Okay, I've got ya.
Just Relax.
Tighter, Wayne.

37:10.344 --> 37:12.279
Okay, is that--
is that okay?

37:12.346 --> 37:15.883
Tighter.
Wayne, hold me tight.
How's that?

37:15.950 --> 37:18.118
Now, kiss me.

37:18.185 --> 37:20.754
Please. Again.

37:23.123 --> 37:25.292
I've waited--

37:32.433 --> 37:34.568
What the hell's the matter
with this elevator?

37:34.635 --> 37:37.972
Uh-Oh.
Must be jammed
between floors again.

37:38.038 --> 37:41.375
I've been waiting five minutes.
I've had a long day in surgery.
I'd like to go home.

37:41.442 --> 37:44.678
I have the key.

37:44.745 --> 37:47.081
This usually works.

37:51.919 --> 37:54.221
This usually works.

37:54.288 --> 37:56.690
What a rathole this is.

37:56.757 --> 37:58.692
Get someone in here
to fix that thing.

37:58.759 --> 38:01.662
Yes, Dr. Craig.

38:01.729 --> 38:04.732
- [ dings ]
- [ dings ]

38:04.798 --> 38:07.334
[ Fiscus ]
Oh, no. Oh, no.
Please Stop.

38:07.401 --> 38:09.336
Please Stop.

38:09.403 --> 38:12.273
<i>No, don't stop.</i>

38:14.341 --> 38:17.411
Ah, there it goes.

38:17.478 --> 38:19.346
[ dings ]

38:22.483 --> 38:24.451
Dr. Fiscus.

38:26.253 --> 38:29.557
Goin' down?

38:29.623 --> 38:31.592
<i>[ Zips up zipper ]</i>

38:37.431 --> 38:39.800
Hey.
Hey.
What are you doing here?

38:39.867 --> 38:41.802
It's 8:00.
You said 8:00.

38:41.869 --> 38:44.905
Oh, right.
Well, listen, I told Chandler
I'd cover for him.

38:44.972 --> 38:46.907
His wife's sick, and--
Oh, Jack!

38:46.974 --> 38:48.976
We finally both get
the same night off, and--

38:49.043 --> 38:52.446
It's a joke.
I'm only kidding.

38:52.513 --> 38:55.983
Good.
Whoa. Look out.

38:56.050 --> 38:58.519
We're goin' to
durgin-Park for lobster.

38:58.586 --> 39:01.388
Okay.
Okay?

39:02.957 --> 39:05.826
I say durgin-Park,
and all you say is "Okay"?

39:05.893 --> 39:10.831
well, I was kind of hoping
that maybe we could go home.

39:10.898 --> 39:12.499
Home.
Mm-hmm.

39:12.566 --> 39:14.501
I thought you wanted
to go someplace Special.

39:14.568 --> 39:19.607
Jack, you and I home
alone together is special.
It practically never happens.

39:19.673 --> 39:23.544
Oh, no, I distinctly remember
One humid night last August.

39:23.611 --> 39:25.813
Mm-Mmm. July.

39:25.879 --> 39:29.450
I remember you spent August
in the emergency room.

39:29.516 --> 39:33.087
That's right.
It was air-Conditioned.

39:33.153 --> 39:35.789
Let's stop off
and get some Champagne.

39:38.425 --> 39:41.528
I'm way ahead of you.

39:41.595 --> 39:43.564
Our Stop.

40:18.566 --> 40:21.969
<i>[ woman on P.A. ]
Dr. Fiscus, 1128.</i>

40:22.036 --> 40:24.905
<i>Dr. Fiscus, 1128.</i>

40:49.096 --> 40:51.932
Uh, your brother called and said
he's gonna be in town
this weekend...

40:51.999 --> 40:54.969
and wanted to know
if he could stay with us,
and I said, "Sure. Why not?"

40:55.035 --> 41:00.441
Sure. That's fine. Oh, uh,
Peter and Myra White want us
to come for dinner next week.

41:00.507 --> 41:02.843
Sounds like fun.

41:02.910 --> 41:05.346
Come on.
They're nice people.
Yeah, I know.

41:05.412 --> 41:07.781
They're just going
through a rough Patch.

41:07.848 --> 41:10.351
Jack Morrison--
defender of the underdog.

41:10.417 --> 41:13.587
Well, he's under
a lot of pressure.
So are you.

41:13.654 --> 41:16.023
And he's struggling
to make ends meet.
So are you.

41:16.090 --> 41:19.560
He has a baby.
So do you.

41:19.627 --> 41:22.129
You're kidding.
Mm-Mmm.

41:22.196 --> 41:25.299
Man!
[ Laughs ]

41:34.909 --> 41:39.179
why do you think
I bought the Champagne?

41:39.246 --> 41:42.716
Wait a minute.
You're-You're-You're pregnant.
You can't, uh-- you can't drink.

41:42.783 --> 41:44.718
Just one.
Not one.

41:46.787 --> 41:49.723
Oh. Yeah!

41:55.496 --> 41:57.598
<i>[ tv, indistinct ]</i>

42:03.904 --> 42:05.873
Hey.

42:08.008 --> 42:10.244
Kids said you were
up here in Bed.

42:10.311 --> 42:14.682
Little, uh, late for a nap
and early for bed, isn't it?

42:16.850 --> 42:19.687
You letting 'em
watch tv?

42:19.753 --> 42:21.722
For a little while.

42:23.924 --> 42:28.896
[ sighs ]
Well, Barry Goodwin's
thinking of leaving the firm.

42:28.963 --> 42:31.065
Some Headhunter's
after him.

42:34.101 --> 42:37.504
Our garbage Disposal's
still broken.

42:37.571 --> 42:39.873
I thought it was supposed
to be fixed by noon?

42:39.940 --> 42:43.611
They didn't fix it.
Well, let's junk the thing.

42:45.579 --> 42:47.548
[ sighs ]

42:50.150 --> 42:53.220
[ sighs ]
I, um--

42:53.287 --> 42:56.190
I was talking to
one of the secretaries
at the office today,

42:56.257 --> 43:00.728
and she, um--
she knows a couple
that have a--

43:00.794 --> 43:02.663
a down's child.

43:02.730 --> 43:04.698
I did it.

43:07.301 --> 43:09.136
I had the abortion.

43:24.618 --> 43:26.820
Tell the girls
to turn off the Tv.

43:30.391 --> 43:32.359
Okay.

43:39.833 --> 43:42.236
<i>[ rain falling ]</i>

43:43.904 --> 43:46.206
â™ªâ™ª [ man singing opera
in Italian ]

43:59.520 --> 44:01.422
listen.

44:18.105 --> 44:22.109
[ speaking italian ]

44:30.284 --> 44:35.656
"Forever now, my dream
of Love is ended.

44:35.723 --> 44:38.726
"When the day breaks,
I die in desperation.

44:38.792 --> 44:42.529
<i>I die in desperation."
That's beautiful.</i>

44:54.174 --> 44:58.078
When I was a little boy
in New York,

44:58.145 --> 45:02.016
my father used to take me to
the metropolitan opera house.

45:04.518 --> 45:06.654
The old one at
Broadway and 39th Street.

45:08.289 --> 45:12.092
<i>Such a beautiful building.
It's gone now,</i>

45:12.159 --> 45:17.431
and in its place
is an office building,
all glass and steel.

45:17.498 --> 45:19.466
Shiny material.

45:22.770 --> 45:25.472
Every week,
we'd go to the met,

45:25.539 --> 45:29.944
and he'd get standing room
'cause we didn't have
enough money for seats.

45:30.010 --> 45:35.883
<i>My father and I,
every week,</i>

45:35.950 --> 45:41.355
we'd stand and watch
puccini, verdi,

45:41.422 --> 45:44.325
mozart,

45:44.391 --> 45:46.360
Wagner.

45:48.829 --> 45:51.031
And my father would Cry.

45:55.502 --> 45:57.471
Once, I asked him,
"Why are you crying, Papa?"

45:59.340 --> 46:01.208
<i>and he turned to me
 and said,</i>

46:01.275 --> 46:06.046
"be quiet. Listen."

46:16.790 --> 46:20.094
I'm 72 years old now
and dying of Cancer.

46:22.062 --> 46:24.398
Ironic, isn't it?

46:24.465 --> 46:29.169
A distinguished liver man
like myself betrayed
by his own liver.

46:32.239 --> 46:35.709
With Radiation and chemotherapy,
I'd have a slightly
better chance,

46:35.776 --> 46:40.547
but the nausea, diarrhea,
stomach cramps--

46:42.716 --> 46:46.220
I'll be septicemic
from skin infections.

46:48.289 --> 46:52.593
The slightest cold
could easily turn to pneumonia
and finish me off in a week.

46:54.995 --> 46:58.432
- What are you gonna do?
- I'm not sure.

47:14.381 --> 47:17.084
- You know what I think?
- Tell me.

47:17.151 --> 47:19.553
You should see a doctor.

47:50.751 --> 47:53.754
Howdy, doctor.
I was just thinkin'
about you.

47:53.821 --> 47:57.157
- You tired?
- tired?

47:57.224 --> 47:59.526
What could I have been doin'
all day long to be tired?

47:59.593 --> 48:02.196
Word around this hospital
is you play gin Rummy.

48:02.263 --> 48:04.999
Gin rummy?
That's my game.

48:09.536 --> 48:12.773
<i>[ sets cards on table ]
you've got the cards.
[ chuckling ]</i>

48:12.840 --> 48:14.775
How about that?

48:14.842 --> 48:18.145
All righty.
I love playin' gin rummy.

48:18.212 --> 48:20.481
Well, the idea is,
you give me the good ones.

48:20.547 --> 48:23.751
Got to save some
for myself, you know.

48:23.817 --> 48:26.654
Oh-- Oh, very good.
I can tell.

48:26.720 --> 48:29.790
[ chuckling ]
Oh, I can tell
by the feel.

48:29.857 --> 48:32.793
Where are you from, doc?
New York.

48:32.860 --> 48:34.828
New York, huh?

48:34.895 --> 48:38.232
I've been there once.

48:38.299 --> 48:40.267
Shall we?

49:15.603 --> 49:16.870
[ Mews ]
